                        <td>
                        
                            As part of STEG&#39;s third annual conference, Tim Phillips recorded a series of podcasts with researchers presenting at the conference. The <a href="https://steg.cepr.org/resources/podcasts" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Conversations on Transformation</a> series investigates some of the most important new research in structural transformation, growth and economic development.<br/>
<br/>
The series kicks off with Adnan Khan, FCDO&#39;s Chief Economist, discussing how we can effectively put research into practice. Through the remaining four episodes, the series explores recent structural transformation research touching on new insights in industrial policy, urban adaptation to rising sea levels, the FDI and domestic firm impacts of new export opportunities, and the impact of Chinese imports on African manufacturing. Find out more on the podcasts and their respective papers below!<br/>
<br/>
We thank Adnan Khan, Nathan Lane, Allan Hsiao, Nina Pavcnik, and Marina Ngoma for contributing to the series.

